#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"Pass a dict of ``{label: 1D tensor}`` for static side-by-side panels; pass "
"``{label: list_of_tensors}`` to render an MP4/GIF animation (needs "
"``pyvista``)."
msgstr ""
"传入 ``{label: 1D tensor}`` 字典可得到静态的并排面板；传入 ``{label: list_of_tensors}`` 则可渲染出"
" MP4/GIF 动画（需要 ``pyvista``\\ ）。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/meshes.rst:366 2cf8b2ee359f4d70865665600cfab2ae
msgid "Two trigonometric fields rendered side by side on a rectangle mesh"
msgstr "在矩形网格上并排渲染的两个三角函数场"

#: ../../source/user_guide/meshes.rst:371 172d32abe2f24f7792c54ff0bc31100b
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"``mesh.plot({...})`` with a multi-key dict renders one panel per field; each"
" panel inherits a colourbar scaled to its own data range."
msgstr "用一个多键字典调用 ``mesh.plot({...})`` 时，会为每个场渲染一个面板；每个面板都会继承一个按其自身数据范围缩放的色条。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/meshes.rst:375 89bcaf8e527a440daae08d2fede699a8
msgid ""
"By default :meth:`~tensormesh.Mesh.plot` only colour-fills the elements. "
"Pass ``show_mesh=True`` to overlay the mesh wireframe (and, at ``order ≥ "
"2``, the interpolation nodes) on top of the field — useful for sanity-"
"checking a freshly solved problem:"
msgstr ""
"默认情况下，\\ :meth:`~tensormesh.Mesh.plot` 只对单元进行颜色填充。传入 ``show_mesh=True`` "
"可在场之上叠加网格线框（在 ``order ≥ 2`` 时还会叠加插值节点）—— 这对于检查刚刚求解完的问题是否合理很有用："

#: ../../source/user_guide/meshes.rst:384 b08e011335f04326b20415e47c04aa77
msgid ""
"Scalar nodal field rendered on a triangular mesh with wireframe overlay"
msgstr "在三角形网格上叠加线框渲染的标量节点场"

#: ../../source/user_guide/meshes.rst:389 a8fcd3bdeb514b2c82c88dc865e40a43
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"``mesh.plot({\"u\": u}, show_mesh=True)`` on a tri mesh. Without "
"``show_mesh=True`` the same call would show only the smooth colour fill, "
"with no triangle edges or interpolation nodes drawn."
msgstr ""
"在三角形网格上调用 ``mesh.plot({\"u\": u}, show_mesh=True)``\\ 。若不加 "
"``show_mesh=True``\\ ，同样的调用将只显示平滑的颜色填充，而不绘制任何三角形边或插值节点。"

#: ../../source/user_guide/meshes.rst:393 bfbff8066ec54fbc9e358e4269ef6ab5
msgid ""
"For a deep dive on visualization, including 3D deformation plots and "
